  "texts": [
    "This paper explores the differences between SMEs and LLM-as-a-judge in evaluating domain-specific tasks that require expert knowledge.",
    "Our findings reveal that it is important to design evaluation systems to keep SME-in-the-loop, and our results highlight the strengths and weaknesses identified in the evaluations between LLM and SMEs.",
    "We also provide an empirical understanding of the factors that SMEs care about during the evaluation process that differ from LLMs.",
    "Our analysis suggests implications that should be considered for evaluating systems in domain-specific tasks, such as integrating SME-in-the-loop and preference tuning or RLHF, developing frameworks on where to best integrate expertise, and using LLM expert personas to improve judgement alignment.",
    "Ultimately, this work contributes to the discussion on SME-driven evaluation, offering insights to enhance alignment between human experts and LLMs in interactive systems. 7.1."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}